Yes. Moreover, `package` in the Scala parse tree is a container for all of the other parsed nodes even when it does not have curly braces.

Thus:

```
package org.pantsbuild
package foo

object Grok
```

is equivalent to:

```
package org.pantsbuild {
  package foo {
    object Grok { 
    }
  }
}
```

Thus there is no single package, but rather potentially many. It made more sense to just prefix the package to each identifier and just output fully-qualified identifiers.

