Adding a check for these "*showstopper*" issues is a nice improvement.  However, I would prefer if we only check the actual deliverable ``cmd2`` source code in the **cmd2** directory.  

As you pointed out, if we also apply these checks to code in the **examples** or **tests** directories, we will run into issues with ``app`` and ``self`` being undefined names.  This is a side-effect of the somewhat unconventional way in which ``cmd2`` supports Python scripting within ``cmd2`` applications.  These Python scripts which use ``app`` and ``self`` are ONLY intended to ever be run inside ``cmd2``'s scripting engine and not within a generic Python interpreter.

@cclauss What do you think?

@kmvanbrunt @kotfu @anselor Do any of you have any bright ideas how to make a small modification to the ``cmd2`` code so that ``flake8`` doesn't warn about ``app`` and/or ``self`` being undefined names in our example scripts and tests?

